page.title: 11INDUSTRY AROUND KEMPSEY.
page.content: Industry in North Kempsey consists only of a sawmill/timber yard, a nursery and Astons coach company. The sawmill has been in business for about 20 years and manufactures various items such as farm fencing, gates, and other useful pieces of work. The mill is split up into two different businesses, a pine factory, and a timber yard. Nine people altogether are employed. Four work in the pine factory, and make furniture such as chairs, tables, and cupboards, and three are employed in the timber yard making general building material. The timber yard has been in business since March 1985 and seems to be doing reasonably well. A reason for this is that they are not simply producing timber for local agricultural needs but are also supplying local industry and home needs as well.
